The 80th floor of the Aon Building is The Mid-America Club. I've been a member for many years and this place is by far one of the best private clubs to join. The atmosphere is elegant. The food is 5 Star as well as the staff. It's a great place for business and pleasure. The views from that height is absolutely incredible day and night. You can see all of Downtown Chicago and all the history it contains! I highly recommend that you contact them regarding membership. I hope to see you there!! Rick is a great guy and the new Manager of the club. Tell him that I referred you and you'll be in very capable hands!
Good venue but not as good as the Metropolitan Club.

Very disappointing.  I have enjoyed dining at the Mid-America Club in the past and would even consider it an ideal event venue.  They don't always have reservations open, so I was excited to book a reservation for a special evening, tonight (October 27), over two weeks in advance on October 12.  I received confirmation from OpenTable and emails on October 13 and yesterday, October 26.  I also received a text message confirmation of my reservation yesterday on October 26 which I responded to and confirmed.  Then, today, 5 hours before my reservation time, I receive an email from someone at another Club, letting me know that my reservation is cancelled due to a special event that closed the club and was planned long ago.  They offered to accommodate me at another Club which is not nearly the experience I had in mind.  Needless to say, this is not only very disappointing but also very embarrassing to have my plans destroyed on the day when they could have (1) not accepted the reservation in the first place and (2) delivered the news somewhere before 5 hours to dinner time (a week ago maybe? at least?)... This is a far less than ideal guest experience and very inconsiderate to a guest with special plans in place for two weeks.

Wonderful steak and lobster Friday night special. The dining room was quiet and wait staff was attentive. The view from 80 stories up was stupendous. Navy Pier was in sight. Cityscape at night is beautiful.
Awesome venue. Great view of the city. Food was delicious. Staff was friendly.

Well this is definitely the place to be. Are you looking for a great scenery at a perfect locations with and amazing view of the World, than the Mid-America Club is where its at. A place for a one night romantic scenery with your significant other or to enjoy with a group of friends. Whom ever you come with to this place this is where memories are build and last a lifetime! It also becomes part of your lifestyle you grow with people you meet a place where you can network build relationships with the staff and management and other people who come just to enjoy a lovely night!  I recommend this place to everyone! It's a must try and experience if only just one time!!!
Friendly people in a building with a gorgeous view of Chicago. Seemed like a chill place for the executive types of the world to take a break.

You want to talk about eating in the sky well how about eating on the 80th floor of the AON Building at the Mid America Club. One of my all time favorite places to go for some delicious dining, great atmosphere where the staff is very friendly and Chef can prepare some of the best food I have ever tasted. If you want a view of Chicago well look no further than at the Mid America Club because I can guarantee you will have the view and food of a lifetime. This coming from the Richlatino Chicagorican Fedora Hat wearer who speaks Spanglish not Spanish.
Befriend someone with a membership to this place because the views are amazing.
Best views of the city, afterwards, everything is awesome!

A terrific venue for a meal, a networking event or charitable fundraiser!  Perched high above the city, this place offers terrific views of Grant & Millennium Parks, the lakefront and the city!  The staff is friendly, service with a smile and the regular members very welcoming as they encourage others to take advantage of this oasis in the city!  Definitely worth a visit!

Found this place on Travelzoo!  This is another amazing restaurant with a perfect view of the city.  Different from The Signature room, the food is fantastic (I'm not saying that the food isn't good @ The Sign Room).  Tried the meat dishes, the chef knows the right way to cook a rare meat.  Really recommend to go during the summer on Wed or Sat nights, so you can enjoying the Navy Pier's fireworks.
